The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Nation at a Glance

 I-Day traffic regulations

 New delhi (PTI): Elaborate arrangements have been made in the capital for Independence Day. 

 Special arrangements have been made to regulate traffic in areas around Red Fort, from where the Prime Minister will address the nation.

 We have made... arrangements to regulate traffic for the August 15 celebrations and about 1,300 traffic personnel will be manning the Delhi roads, joint commissioner of police (traffic) Qamar Ahmed said.

 He said all major roads leading to the fort will be closed to traffic from 5 am to 9 am on Tuesday and advised motorists using Ring Road to use Aurobindo Marg, Safdarjung Road, Mother Teresa Road and Rani Jhansi Road to reach north Delhi and vice versa. 

 Ring Road would be off limits to all heavy commercial vehicles from 2 pm on Monday to 11 am on Tuesday. 

 Traffic to major hospitals and metro stations will remain unchanged but parking will not be allowed outside New Delhi and old Delhi railway stations from Monday evening till Tuesday.

 Lashkar militants killed

 Srinagar (PTI): Three Lashkar-e-Toiba militants were killed in an encounter with security forces in the Handwara area of Kupwara district, a defence spokesman said.

 On specific information, the army laid a cordon in Ringpath village on Saturday. A search operation was started during which the ultras opened fire and the troops retaliated. Three AK rifles, two radio sets, one grenade launcher, four grenades and three Chinese hand grenades were found on them. 

 Army rescue

 Jammu (PTI): The army has rescued nearly 300 foreign tourists marooned in the flood-hit Ladakh region, army sources said.

 Four persons from the US were airlifted in a chopper from the Zanskar area while others were rescued from Kargil and Leh districts during an eight-day-long operation in Ladakh, the sources said.

 Prison clash

 Sonepat (PTI): Four prisoners were seriously injured in a clash between two rival groups in the district jail on Saturday, police sources said. The injured were returning to their barracks after an evening walk when they were allegedly attacked with iron rods, pipes and knives.

 Convict breather

 New Delhi (PTI): Delhi High Court has suspended the 10-year jail sentence of Jordanian Robert Saleem, who was convicted of raping a doctor four years ago. 

 Selvan, a master weaver of a textile house in Kerala, has woven a sari 1,585 feet long and 4.35 feet wide in an attempt to enter the Guinness Book of Records. 




